message.content: Since $a_1$ is inversely proportional to $b_1$ while $a_2$ is inversely proportional to $b_2$, we have $$a_1b_1 = a_2b_2.$$We also have $$\frac{a_1}{a_2} = \frac23,$$so $\frac{a_2}{a_1} = \frac 32$. Substitute $a_2 = \frac 32 a_1$ into the first equation to obtain $$1 \cdot b_1 = \frac 32 a_1b_2.$$Simplifying gives $b_1 = \frac 23 a_1b_2$, so $\frac {b_1}{b_2} = \frac 23 a_1 = \boxed{2}$.
